<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648128>
    dc:description "Figure 1: Vaejovis halli sp. nov. Holotype female in natural habitat." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648128/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648130>
    dc:description "Figures 2–3: Vaejovis halli, sp. nov. 2. Holotype female ventral and dorsal views. 3. Paratype male dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648130/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648132>
    dc:description "Figures 4-9: Vaejovis halli, sp. nov. 4, 5, 7-9, holotype female. 4. Carapace. 5. Telson. 6. Paratype male, pectines and sternites; 7. Pectines and sternites. 8, 9. Metasoma and telson, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648132/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648134>
    dc:description "Figure 10: Vaejovis halli, sp. nov. Female holotype trichobothrial pattern." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648134/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648136>
    dc:description "Figure 11: Vaejovis halli, sp. nov., male paratype. Right hemispermatophore (submerged in alcohol). Left. Dorsal view showing the short bifurcated lamellar hook emanating from the dorsal trough and the distal lamellar crest. Top Right. Close-up of lamellar hook. Bottom Right. Mating plug, dorsal view, showing the slightly sclerotized smooth barb (from left hemispermatophore, reversed in image)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648136/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648140>
    dc:description "Figure 13: Vaejovis halli sp. nov. female with first instar juveniles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648140/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648142>
    dc:description "Figure 14: Vaejovis halli sp. nov. habitat." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648142/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648144>
    dc:description "Figure 15: Map of Arizona and extreme western New Mexico showing the type locality of the twelve Vaejovis species discussed in this paper, including new species Vaejovis halli. Localities are divided into those species exhibiting seven inner denticles (ID) on the chelal movable finger (white rectangles with black lettering) and those with primarily six ID denticles (black rectangles with white lettering). Seven IDs: 1 = V. jonesi, 2 = V. lapidicola, 3 = V. paysonensis, 4 = V. crumpi, 5 = V. bigelowi. Six IDs: 6 = V. vorhiesi, 7 = V. cashi, 8 = V. feti, 9 = V. deboerae, 10 = V. electrum, 11 = V. tenuipalpus, and 12 = V. halli, sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4648144/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

